<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFF3E51EEBE7B4497" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[174,352,387,409]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="87 - 92" refId="ref3929" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1989. A review of palaearctic species of the genus Hendrella (Diptera, Tephritidae). Zoologichesky Zhurnal, 68 (6), 87 - 92 [In Russian, with English summary]." type="journal article" year="1989">Korneyev 1989: 87</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
(key and revision of 7 species); 
<treatmentCitation id="3C3A108FFFD3FFCAFD0151EEBC9C4497" author="Norrbom, A. L. &amp; Carroll, L. E. &amp; Thompson, F. C. &amp; White, I. M. &amp; Freidberg, A." box="[657,903,387,409]" page="157" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" year="1999">
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFD0151EEBC9C4497" author="Norrbom, A. L. &amp; Carroll, L. E. &amp; Thompson, F. C. &amp; White, I. M. &amp; Freidberg, A." box="[657,903,387,409]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="65 - 299" refId="ref4106" refString="Norrbom, A. L., Carroll, L. E., Thompson, F. C., White, I. M., Freidberg, A. 1999. Systematic Database of Names. In: Thompson, F. C., ed. Fruit Fly Expert Identification System and Systematic Information Database. Backhuis Publishers, Leiden (1998), 65 - 299 (Myia, 9)." type="book chapter" year="1999">Norrbom et al., 1999: 157</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
(catalogue).
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFCAFF7351D2BDB447B4" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">D e s c r i p t i o n. H e a d in profile slightly higher than long. Frons narrowing from ocellar triangle to lunule and with fine yellowish setulae on anterior half. Eye oval. Gena narrower than length of antenna. Antenna somewhat shorter than face, first flagellomere rounded or pointed apicodorsally, less than twice as long as wide, arista with short pubescence. Proboscis capitate, palp unmodified. Two pairs of dark and rarely an additional white frontal and two orbital setae present; posterior orbital seta whitish yellow and reclinate; medial vertical seta brown to black; lateral vertical seta white, shorter than anterior orbital seta. Postocular setae mixed long and short.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F5816515FFD3FFC9FF7352D2BD9A4464" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="217" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFCAFF7352D2BD734634" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Thorax. Ground color yellowish brown to dark brown with notopleural area yellow. Dorsocentral setae situated near transverse suture; posterior notopleural seta concolorous with anterior one. Scutellum microtrichose, with one pair of setae. Anepimeral seta black, brown or yellow. Scutal setulae white.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFCAFF735352BBCA46D4" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">
Wing. 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFED3532DBE894654" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[323,402,832,858]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Aciura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFED3532DBE894654" box="[323,402,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Aciura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus id="6220883CFFD3FFCAFE0A5352BED44654" box="[410,463,831,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">type</typeStatus>
pattern including yellowish brown to dark brown pattern with several hyaline spots. Vein 
<specimenCode id="ED3D9EE5FFD3FFCAFE785332BD19468E" box="[488,514,863,896]" collectionCode="R" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">
R 
<subScript id="211F34DBFFD3FFCAFE6A531FBD19468E" attach="left" box="[506,514,882,896]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">1</subScript>
</specimenCode>
dorsally with a gap in row of setulae at level of Sc apex. Costal vein with 1–2 strong setae before costal break, costal setae not more than 1.5 times as long as width of costa; cell r 
<subScript id="211F34DBFFD3FFCAFE2953DFBEDA46CE" attach="left" box="[441,449,946,960]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">1</subScript>
with 1–2 marginal hyaline spots. Distance between crossveins r-m and dm-cu slightly longer than r-m crossvein. Cell bcu with short posteroapical extension.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFCAFF7353B2BB254194" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">A b d o m e n. Yellowish brown to completely black. Epandrium oval with non-modified surstyli; two pairs of prensisetae present; preglans area of phallus bare; subapical lobe of glans neither sclerotized nor trumpet-like; glans with conspicuously sclerotized basal part; apical membranous lobes shorter than basal sclerotized part. Dorsal side of eversible membrane with a medial bare groove between two rows of scales; scales on ventral side of eversible membrane forming narrow isolated stripe. Aculeus pointed apically.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFCAFF7354F2BEE34054" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFE1754F2BEE141B7" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1938" box="[391,506,1183,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFE1754F2BEE141B7" box="[391,506,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Hendrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD2254F2BC3B41B7" authorityName=": Hendel" authorityYear="1927" box="[690,800,1183,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Tephrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFD2254F2BC3B41B7" box="[690,800,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Tephrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sharing similar wing pattern and presence of 2–3 frontal and two orbital and only one scutellar setae, differing from it by having two frontal setae (sometimes a short white seta anterior to them) and posterior orbital seta whitish yellow (2–3 large frontal setae in 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFC8A5492BC934017" authorityName=": Hendel" authorityYear="1927" box="[794,904,1279,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Tephrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFC8A5492BC934017" box="[794,904,1279,1305]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Tephrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and posterior orbital seta is brown). In 
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFEA65572BEAB4037" box="[310,432,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFEA65572BEB74037" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1938" box="[310,428,1311,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hendrella</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
dorsocentral setae are situated at suture, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFBB75572BB8E4037" authorityName=": Hendel" authorityYear="1927" box="[1063,1173,1311,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Tephrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFBB75572BB8E4037" box="[1063,1173,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Tephrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are closer to supraalar setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFCAFF735532BDED4334" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">
T a x o n o m i c p o s i t i o n. 
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFD8A5532BC324074" author="Norrbom, A. L. &amp; Carroll, L. E. &amp; Thompson, F. C. &amp; White, I. M. &amp; Freidberg, A." box="[538,809,1375,1402]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="65 - 299" refId="ref4106" refString="Norrbom, A. L., Carroll, L. E., Thompson, F. C., White, I. M., Freidberg, A. 1999. Systematic Database of Names. In: Thompson, F. C., ed. Fruit Fly Expert Identification System and Systematic Information Database. Backhuis Publishers, Leiden (1998), 65 - 299 (Myia, 9)." type="book chapter" year="1999">Norrbom et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
classified the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFB8C5532BB8E4074" box="[1052,1173,1375,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Tephritini">Tephritini</taxonomicName>
into six main groups and included 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD885512BD904097" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1938" box="[536,651,1407,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFD885512BD904097" box="[536,651,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Hendrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD245512BC284097" box="[692,819,1407,1433]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Meruliaceae" genus="Spathulina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFD245512BC284097" box="[692,819,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Spathulina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of the 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFC475512BB484094" box="[983,1107,1407,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Tephritini">Tephritini</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFBCF5512BFE140B4" author="Korneyev, V. A." pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="549 - 580" refId="ref3972" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1999. Phylogeny of the subfamily Tephritinae: relationships of the tribes and subtribes. In: Aluja, M. &amp; Norrbom, A. L., eds. Fruit Flies (Tephritidae): Phylogeny and Evolution of Behaviour. CRC Press, Boca Raton, 549 - 580." type="book chapter" year="1999">Korneyev (1999)</bibRefCitation>
studied cladistic relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD3A55F2BC2E40B4" box="[682,821,1439,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tephritinae">Tephritinae</taxonomicName>
and placed the genera allied to 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFF3E55D2BE0D40D7" box="[174,278,1471,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oedaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFF3E55D2BE0D40D7" box="[174,278,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Oedaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFEBA55D2BE8640D7" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1938" box="[298,413,1471,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFEBA55D2BE8640D7" box="[298,413,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Hendrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFE2155D2BD0C40D7" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[433,535,1471,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Dithryca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFE2155D2BD0C40D7" box="[433,535,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Dithryca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFDCF55ADBDA240D7" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1873" box="[607,697,1472,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Eurosta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFDCF55ADBDA240D7" box="[607,697,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Eurosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD7B55D2BC7240D4" box="[747,873,1471,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dithrycini">Dithrycini</taxonomicName>
. Monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFBA655D2BBAA40D4" box="[1078,1201,1471,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dithrycini">Dithrycini</taxonomicName>
is supported by a unique pattern of scales on the eversible membrane and similarity of aculeus shape (
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFF6F5592BEA74314" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[255,444,1535,1562]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="549 - 580" refId="ref3972" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1999. Phylogeny of the subfamily Tephritinae: relationships of the tribes and subtribes. In: Aluja, M. &amp; Norrbom, A. L., eds. Fruit Flies (Tephritidae): Phylogeny and Evolution of Behaviour. CRC Press, Boca Raton, 549 - 580." type="book chapter" year="1999">Korneyev, 1999</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, all known host plants of 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFCEA5592BCEE4314" box="[890,1013,1535,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dithrycini">Dithrycini</taxonomicName>
belong to the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFF3E5672BE564334" authorityName="Cassini" authorityYear="1819" box="[174,333,1567,1594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Anthemideae">Anthemideae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFECD5672BEA04337" box="[349,443,1567,1593]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Achillea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFECD5672BEA04337" box="[349,443,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Achillea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFE59564DBD204334" box="[457,571,1568,1594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFE59564DBD204334" box="[457,571,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFDE55672BDFE4337" box="[629,741,1567,1593]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFDE55672BDFE4337" box="[629,741,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Santolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFCAFF735652BD9143F4" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">
Molecular studies based on mitochondrial 16S rDNA showed that Nearctic 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFBE6562DBBCB4357" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1873" box="[1142,1232,1600,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Eurosta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFBE6562DBBCB4357" box="[1142,1232,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Eurosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFF72560DBE524374" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1932" box="[226,329,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Aciurina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFF72560DBE524374" box="[226,329,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Aciurina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not closely related to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD675632BC444377" box="[759,863,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oedaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFD675632BC444377" box="[759,863,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Oedaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFC595632BFE84394" authority="(Han et al., 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Han" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dithrycini">
Dithrycini (
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFBC45632BFF04394" author="Han, H. - Y. &amp; Ro, K. - E. &amp; McPheron, B. A." pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="78 - 88" refId="ref3789" refString="Han, H. - Y., Ro, K. - E., McPheron, B. A. 2006. Molecular phylogeny of the subfamily Tephritinae (Diptera: Tephritidae) based on mitochondrial 16 S rDNA sequences. Molecules and Cells, 22 (1), 78 - 88." type="journal article" year="2006">Han et al., 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but most diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD185612BDE04397" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1938" box="[648,763,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFD185612BDE04397" box="[648,763,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Hendrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still support its placement in 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFBC65612BBCA4394" box="[1110,1233,1663,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dithrycini">Dithrycini</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFF2656F2BE6E43B4" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[182,373,1695,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="549 - 580" refId="ref3972" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1999. Phylogeny of the subfamily Tephritinae: relationships of the tribes and subtribes. In: Aluja, M. &amp; Norrbom, A. L., eds. Fruit Flies (Tephritidae): Phylogeny and Evolution of Behaviour. CRC Press, Boca Raton, 549 - 580." type="book chapter" year="1999">Korneyev, 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFE1456F2BD9243B4" author="Korneyev, V. A. &amp; Zwolfer, H. &amp; Seitz, A." box="[388,649,1695,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="321 - 371" refId="ref4031" refString="Korneyev, V. A., Zwolfer, H., Seitz, A. 2004. Phylogenetic relationships, ecology and ecological genetics of cecidogeneous Tephritidae. In: Raman, A., Schaefer, C. W., Withers, T. M., eds. Biology, Ecology and Evolution of Gall-Inducing Arthropods. Science Publishers, Enfield, New Hampshire, USA, 321 - 371." type="book chapter" year="2004">Korneyev et al., 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFD0E56F2BC4543B4" author="Hancock, D. L." box="[670,862,1695,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="111 - 116" refId="ref3845" refString="Hancock, D. L. 2001. Systematic notes on the genera of Australian and some non-Australian Tephritinae (Diptera: Tephritidae). Australian Entomologist, 28 (4), 111 - 116." type="journal article" year="2001">Hancock (2001)</bibRefCitation>
assigned 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFC4756F2BB2443B7" box="[983,1087,1695,1721]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oedaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFC4756F2BB2443B7" box="[983,1087,1695,1721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Oedaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related genera to the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFE5456D2BD4D43D4" box="[452,598,1727,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Platensinina">Platensinina</taxonomicName>
and noted that 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFC8F56D2BC8943D7" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1938" box="[799,914,1727,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFC8F56D2BC8943D7" box="[799,914,1727,1753]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Hendrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been included in the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFE8556B2BE8E43F4" box="[277,405,1759,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Dithrycina">Dithrycina</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFCAFE2E56B2BD9D43F4" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[446,646,1759,1786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="549 - 580" refId="ref3972" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1999. Phylogeny of the subfamily Tephritinae: relationships of the tribes and subtribes. In: Aluja, M. &amp; Norrbom, A. L., eds. Fruit Flies (Tephritidae): Phylogeny and Evolution of Behaviour. CRC Press, Boca Raton, 549 - 580." type="book chapter" year="1999">Korneyev (1999)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD24369EFFD3FFC9FF735692BD9A4464" blockId="1.[174,1233,447,1850]" lastBlockId="2.[166,1225,175,362]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="217" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">
Biology. Most species of 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFD8C5692BD944217" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1938" box="[540,655,1791,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFD8C5692BD944217" box="[540,655,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Hendrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been collected by sweeping from 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFBCE576DBBCB4214" box="[1118,1232,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFBCE576DBBCB4214" box="[1118,1232,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFF265772BE224234" box="[182,313,1823,1850]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFCAFED15772BEF94234" authorityName="Cassini" authorityYear="1819" box="[321,482,1823,1850]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Anthemideae">Anthemideae</taxonomicName>
) stands. The only hitherto reared species, 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD3FFC9FC2C574DBFC545C4" authority="V. Korneyev, 1989" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Hendrella" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="217" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordida">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD3FFCAFC2C574DBB2F4237" box="[956,1076,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">H.sordida</emphasis>
V. 
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD3FFC9FBC85772BFC545C4" author="Korneyev, V. A." lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="217" pageId="1" pageNumber="216" pagination="87 - 92" refId="ref3929" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1989. A review of palaearctic species of the genus Hendrella (Diptera, Tephritidae). Zoologichesky Zhurnal, 68 (6), 87 - 92 [In Russian, with English summary]." type="journal article" year="1989">Korneyev, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was reared from monothalamic galls on branches of 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD0FFC9FCD050DDBBDE45C4" authority="Krasch." authorityName="Krasch." box="[832,1221,175,202]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="217" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="proceraeformis">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD0FFC9FCD050DDBB7F45C7" box="[832,1124,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">Artemisia proceraeformis</emphasis>
Krasch.
</taxonomicName>
; adults emerge in late July or August and apparently overwinter (
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD0FFC9FC2150A2BBDE45E4" author="Basov, V. M. &amp; Korneyev, V. A." box="[945,1221,207,234]" pageId="2" pageNumber="217" pagination="47 - 51" refId="ref3688" refString="Basov, V. M., Korneyev, V. A. 1987. Exit of tephritid flies (Diptera, Tephritidae) from their larval chambers. Problems of general and molecular biology. Kiev, 6, 47 - 51 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1987">Basov, Korneyev, 1987</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="25A02A1BFFD0FFC9FF365082BFC44404" box="[166,223,239,266]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[161,194,1771,1793]" captionTargetBox="[241,1134,1055,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-381@2.[237,1144,1040,1770]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Hendrella kermanensis sp. n.: 1 — holotype, male, habitus, left; 2 — same, dorsal view; 3 — epandrium and hypandrium, lateral left view; 4 — epandrium, posterior view; 5 — ejaculatory apodeme; 6 — glans of phallus, dorsolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="25A02A1BFFD0FFC9FF7B5082BFE24407" box="[235,249,239,265]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[221,1190,1179,1745]" captionTargetId="figure-471@3.[208,1190,1173,1765]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Hendrella kermanensis sp. n. (1, 3) and H. caloptera (2): 1, 2 — wing (arrows show difference in coloration of costal cell); 3 — galls on Artemisia aucheri (collected together with flies)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454186/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD0FFC9FF7B5082BFE24407" box="[235,249,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD0FFC9FE965082BEA44404" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[262,447,239,266]" pageId="2" pageNumber="217" pagination="87 - 92" refId="ref3929" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1989. A review of palaearctic species of the genus Hendrella (Diptera, Tephritidae). Zoologichesky Zhurnal, 68 (6), 87 - 92 [In Russian, with English summary]." type="journal article" year="1989">Korneyev, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; V. Korneyev, pers. comm.). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD0FFC9FC0D509DBB314407" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1850" box="[925,1066,239,265]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Trypeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caloptera">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD0FFC9FC0D509DBB314407" box="[925,1066,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">H. caloptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected by sweeping on 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD0FFC9FEF9517DBD1E4424" box="[361,517,271,298]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="217" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD0FFC9FEF9517DBEC04424" box="[361,475,272,298]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">Artemisia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
near 
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD0FFC9FDDB5162BDD14427" box="[587,714,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">limonifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D90A4B6FFFD0FFC9FD4B5162BCC44424" author="Korneyev, V. A. &amp; Zwolfer, H. &amp; Seitz, A." box="[731,991,271,298]" pageId="2" pageNumber="217" pagination="321 - 371" refId="ref4031" refString="Korneyev, V. A., Zwolfer, H., Seitz, A. 2004. Phylogenetic relationships, ecology and ecological genetics of cecidogeneous Tephritidae. In: Raman, A., Schaefer, C. W., Withers, T. M., eds. Biology, Ecology and Evolution of Gall-Inducing Arthropods. Science Publishers, Enfield, New Hampshire, USA, 321 - 371." type="book chapter" year="2004">Korneyev et al., 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The life history of other 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD0FFC9FF7C5142BEA34444" box="[236,440,303,330]" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD0FFC9FF7C5142BE444447" box="[236,351,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">Hendrella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
remains almost unknown but they are suspected to induce stem or rhizome galls in other 
<taxonomicName id="7A9B4D1DFFD0FFC9FE3E513DBD9A4464" box="[430,641,335,362]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="217" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="8FEFEA8CFFD0FFC9FE3E513DBD3B4464" box="[430,544,336,362]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="217">Artemisia</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
